# Enforce LF line endings on commit and in the working tree on every platform.
# This kills the CRLF/LF whole-file churn observed in Phase 2 (audit_report.md
# L507-509) where editor normalisation rewrote line endings on touched files.
#
# - `text=auto eol=lf` is the project default: Git auto-detects text vs binary
#   and normalises text files to LF.
# - The explicit `text eol=lf` rules below are belt-and-braces for formats we
#   touch frequently, so a misconfigured editor can't reintroduce CRLF.
# - The `binary` rules declare formats Git must never normalise. None of these
#   are tracked today, but declaring them up-front means future commits Just
#   Work without re-rolling .gitattributes.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Source and config — explicit LF
*.py        text eol=lf
*.pyi       text eol=lf
*.md        text eol=lf
*.toml      text eol=lf
*.yml       text eol=lf
*.yaml      text eol=lf
*.json      text eol=lf
*.cfg       text eol=lf
*.ini       text eol=lf
*.txt       text eol=lf
*.sh        text eol=lf

# Generator outputs — also text, also LF
*.csv       text eol=lf
*.sql       text eol=lf
*.tsv       text eol=lf

# Binary formats — never normalise
*.png       binary
*.jpg       binary
*.jpeg      binary
*.gif       binary
*.ico       binary
*.svg       binary
*.pdf       binary
*.zip       binary
*.gz        binary
*.tar       binary
*.parquet   binary
*.feather   binary
*.xlsx      binary
*.xls       binary
*.pbix      binary
*.pbit      binary
*.db        binary
*.sqlite    binary
*.sqlite3   binary
